narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: This was a subject I wasn't super familiar with, but a great topical introduction to a transatlantic political history and political philosophy moment. Learned a lot about the period, and about the literature surrounding the period.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: The course was strong in political thought and development of federal ideas. Getting a handle on the actual events of the period can be difficult if you don't have a pretty good background though. Sometimes seemed like Prof. Pincus was a little to far out in front of the class, but mostly it was excellent.
Wonderful geographical breadth and excellent readings. The discussion in class, however, was extremely stilted and would have benefitted from greater instructor engagement.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes. Prof. Pincus is a great historian, and Prof. Nakhimovsky is excellent as well. A great primer on the history surrounding the early US and its political structure.
